snippet.textDisplay:
Hey Jeffree! How are you? Seriously, how are you? I can't decide which looks more amazing.. The wig or the fantabulous results we saw Mitchell apply on you with Blood Lust. OOF! I've seen you in many different wigs, but that purple wig is beyond stunning on you. That shade is extremely flattering on you. But then your complexion is to die for anyways. May I ask you several questions please?
1. Should I always use an eyeshadow primer, and which one do you suggest, especially for me and my sensitive allergy eyes.
I learned the hard way that I needn't have a heavy hand with your blushes and eyeshadows. The blush experience was a hilarious disaster but it was my first experience with your quality cosmetics.
2. I am such a fangirl of yours and support everything that is you. I sound dorky but I'm not a stalker fangirl. Just think you're an inspiration for people everywhere to embrace their inner beauty and also to be true to yourself. I hate when people hate on you. I know you don't defending but some people are just ignorant and misinformed and I become beyond shooked.
Rumors, yadda yadda yadda. But Mitchell and you would make such a power couple.
OMG, your sense of humor is epic. I'm a naturally sarcastic gal with a slight sick sense of humor too. Some people find it hard to understand me or don't get me.
I have cheekbones...SOMEWHERE! But I cannot contour worth shit.
Again another question. Sorry.. I absolutely need to know how to get myself one of your iconic Star mirrors.
I need to follow up to find out when I can get myself this epic new palette. God your end look leaves me breathless! Duh! I just heard that Feb 21, is the drop date. I'll be there. But I have yet to get my ass together and try about getting the Conspiracy and Controversy palletes. Will Blood Lust be a limited exclusive palette? Because I'm sure your fans are going to BREAK the internet again trying to get this gorgeous baybee!
I like your Blue Blood pallete as well, but it's an older palette correct? Is it still in production or has it been retired? I had to laugh about your eyebrow struggle. Here's mine. I was using a different eyelash curler than I normally use, something happened, my right hand slipped and HALF of my long eyelashes from my left eye were literally torn off. Not broken off, but RIPPED out! I am shocked to see tho that my lashes have already grown back. It only took a couple weeks, but I was shocked and happy by how quickly they regrew, considering half my lashes were literally ripped out of the roots.
I've wanted a Pomeranian since I was in high school. My heart is sad as I had to euthanize my sick cat several days ago. I would rather eat razors than go thru the emotional pain of having to say goodbye to your pet FOREVER. I'm hoping to move into a 2 bedroom apartment soon, but don't want to stress out the dog if apartment life isn't good for a Pom.
